{
  "stem": "11290.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this was rejected by the Kaiser's-- the Kaiser rejected it, and it was rejected also by some other advisers, because they found out that the Jews had served in the Army as a larger percentage than their percentage of the population.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was so many Jews in the army.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And take 12,000 out of 500,000 were killed, which was a larger percentage than that of the total population. 12,000 Jewish men died at the front.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that was the First World War.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember the First World War.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's so long ago now it's, practically history.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I remember it as it happened, because with all that the deprivation and all the spirit of victory that began first and the sad ending, and the many, many news of dead in every family.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In my own family, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I had-- my father had an uncle who lost three sons out of five.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So that was a big sacrifice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They did.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it must have been underlying-- I'm sure that underlying anti-Semitism was there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But what also made it so fast was that the tremendous power that the Nazis exerted once they took over.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The threat was so great that everybody buckled under.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People did not resist.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "First of all, they really thought that the movement in the beginning would be beneficial for the people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that anti-Semitism was only perhaps a minor feature of the entire rising of the German people to new freedom, a new recognition, and more equal life.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The enthusiasm in the beginning was very, very great.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But at the same time, the-- nobody dared to deviate.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There were so few people that deviated that-- that felt-- that saw what was coming and that understood it.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
